name: McDonald's
address: Jl. Kebo Iwa Selatan No.177X, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
Terrible service but good to see a business employing mentally challenged people.

Update: the people that run this place are severely challenged (in their mental capacities). I was unable to order at the drive thru because of reasons that they could not explain. So I parked and walked inside. I was then unable to order for another 15 minutes (again, for reasons they could not explain).

New update: I would rather die than order from here again. 1 hour waiting for a McDonald‚Äôs order should be illegal.
review 2: The location is easy to find because like McDonald's in general which are mostly on street corners, large space inside or outside the room, parking is also very spacious for cars or motorbikes, health protocols for the new normal are also well implemented, employees are very helpful and friendly  also.
review 3:
One of the best Mc Donalds in Baliüòç
This mcd is located on the corner of South Kebo Iwa street so it's really easy to find. They provide self-service order by using digital monitor. They also have a cafe that sell dessert such as cake and also sweet beverages. Ohya, there is playground ! Your children wouldn't be boring when you visited this mcdüëçüëçüëç
review 4: Just found out that this franchise is open 24 hours. They had 6 outlets (5 Indoor & 1 Outdoor). Overall it was all good and I'm enjoying my meal
review 5: MCDonald at gatsu barat has playground that really helps parents who bring their kids. You can order the food & drink via big screen on the main door/entry. You can also choose online/offline payment within the order process. After finishing it, just take the number besides the screen and wait for your order to deliver to your sits. After finish your eat, please clean up the trash by yourself to the garbage place provided.

name: Puri Saron Hotel Denpasar
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.459 C, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
A very good hotel located in Denpasar. The value for the hotel is excellent. The rooms are quite spacious, the air conditioning works very well, the rooms are clean enough. The toilets on the rooms are also good. The hotel also have free wifi.

The breakfast in the hotel are excellent, they have egg station for the breakfast. The hotel also have a small swimming pool. The hotel have some parking space at the front of the hotel.
review 2: Old building dirty room dirty pool. If youre looking for something cheap, rent a room. Bad value for money
review 3:
Pros:
- Cheap budget hotel in Bali
- Pretty close to Seminyak area with the pretty beach and eateries
- About 1 hour drive from Ngurah Rai airport
- Good size double-bed room
- Pretty pricey breakfast/food. Easy alternative to order via grab to be delivered to the hotel lobby
- Good size bathroom
- Swimming pool by the restaurant

Cons:
- No kettle in the room, so it's pretty annoying when you want to make some coffee or tea
- TV doesn't work or only shows MTV channel but really bad reception.

I think it'll make a big difference to add some convenience to add a kettle in the room. It a small simple thing that make a big difference.
review 4:
Nice room, nice internet, but not have water dispenser for coffee in a room.

I stay for 4 night, all my breakfast was not varied, just fried rice and fried noodle.. only fried rice and noodle..

maybe because the guest are quite. But on my last day, with all people in picture, the breakfast still fried rice and noodle..

Tv not varied, just local TV and I think it use antenna tv, not provider tv..

Room always clean, and nice..
review 5:
The parking place a little bit confusing. Cause i'm here for the workshop so i need to park near  the meeting room, behind the hotel.
But it's easy to find this hotel.

yes

name: Cozy Residence Wedasari Bali
address: Taman Wedasari 1A no 12, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
Cozy Residence is different name for the RedDoorz. It's the same place.

We booked "deluxe room", really don't feel deluxe in anything.

- we got room with no window (just ventilation in the bathroom)
- room smels
- water in sink not working
- water in the toilet not working
- noisy guys in 5 in the morning (mybe it were teenage guys from the reception)
- room looks old and not well maintained (but  + it was kind of clean)
+ bed ok
+ big room
+ soap
review 2: Unique building, old style. Super friendly boys in reception, very helpful and not lazy at all. Bed are very comfortable, nice to sleep here. Just swimming pool are dirty and room not clean enough. But for this cheap price and nice people I can't complain)
review 3: Its very difficult to find out the room.. its just like a puzzle
review 4: Housing Complex, not too crowded, clean and hommy. Located in West of Denpasar center. Close to McD, KFC, Burger King, Mitra 10, Indosat, SPBU, local market...
review 5: Good room residence and good price, big room, price stRt 90k to100k, clean and big toilet/shower

name: Ming Coffee Eatery and Music
address: Jl. Kebo Iwa Utara No.52A, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: Almost every thing was good, food is tasty and price is reasonable, garden is very beautiful but a little noisy because ot is a very family friendly restaurant and it has a children's playing ground.
review 2: I ordered fried noodles but they weren't very tasty, the noodles were too mushy and a little salty. The place is nice, wifi is good.
review 3:
Very nice and comfortable place to eat with your friends and family.
1. The food tastes pretty good not as good as the restaurant that sells the specialty.
2. The service is friendly even though many requests outside the menu are still served well.
3. And the coolest thing is the live music with comfortable seating and atmosphere.
review 4: What a great experience we have here. Friendly staff and great foods!!
review 5: I recently visited  Ming Coffee eatery in kebo iwa street denpasar in Bali and was thoroughly impressed. The atmosphere was delightful, and great food and attentive service from the friendly staff. The place is very pretty and well designed.  I can't wait to come back again with some friends. Thanks again :)

name: Waroeng Spesial Sambal "SS"
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.452, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80118, Indonesia
review 1:
The place is easy to find with a fairly large parking area making it easy to park your vehicle. The food/chili sauce(sambal) varies with different levels of spiciness, the grilled tempeh is highly recommended.
The staff is quite helpful and the service is quite fast, only the place is very hot (even though it has a fan but it doesn't help).
The hand washing place is not clean (I hope the owner pay more attention).
Over all everything is good.

Recommended : Grilled tempeh (for those who like sweet food)

Reasonable priceüëç
review 2: Food took so long! There was no information about how long will you wait! The taste of the food isn't as enjoyable as before! Terong goreng tidak sepenuhnya matang, paru bakar tidak well seasoned. Please do your work on maintaining customer. Will not go here anymore.
review 3: Will be the first and the last to come here again, the food way too slow. Only 3 table at 10.00am took more than 1 hour for my order 2 grill chicken, 2 fried mushroom, 1 cah kangkung. DEFINITELY WONT COMEBACK
review 4: The food n sambal are normal type...each portions are rather palm size clay plates. Could increase  the portioning  l don't mind in price increased too.
review 5: The food was really good, but it was quite hot so maybe more fan ceiling

name: RedDoorz @ Jalan Gatot Subroto Denpasar
address: Jl. Taman Wedasari IA No.12, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: One of the worst, honestly. The toilet was super dirty. There were no toiletries, no kettle, no glasses, even though it was specified in the room description. I had to ask at the reception desk for towels and the guy literally brought them only the next day. They don't speak English, either. The door had trouble closing and the cleanliness was non existent. The wifi did not really work, either. Will not be returning any time soon.
review 2:
Room is dingy, never cleaned, filled with ants and cockroaches.

Constant construction noise during the day, workers sleep near the premise outside at night ..random people that don't live there constantly loitering.

Hot water does not work, toilet was non functional some days. I had to fill the toilet tank with water every time I wanted to flush.

My room was never cleaned...not once. Never been offered to either. The bed sheets made my skin itchy and it was hard to sleep...construction workers making noise till past midnight, roosters waking me up at 6 am then construction begins soon after...

Overall, glad that nightmare is over.
review 3: The location is quite ok near the main road. But the room and the service is bad. This is the worst reddoorz i've ever visited. At first I came, the receptionist seemed ignorance, kept playing game eventhough i was standing in front of the receptionist's desk. Then checked in process only given the payment proof (I booked directly from the website). He wasnt asking for my ID, then he asked me to follow me. After he opened the room, he left without say anything. The room is clean but smelled damp. I give 2 stars only the cleanliness, but it is basic.
review 4: Price for what you get it's ok. But the room smells, and looks more or less clean, but don't look in detail. The swimming pool you really can't use. There is not enough water and it's not clean at all. You have to sign a document: they are not responsible for stuff that disappear from your room...
review 5: Simple but adequate budget hotel, clean and comfortable room, hot shower, good WiFi, everything you need for a night in transit...got a very low price via Agoda, definitely a very good value stay... there's even a swimming pool (or rather dipping pool), very refreshing!

name: Richeese Factory Kebo Iwa
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.449, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: The location is great, but the service was quite slow. It took us 20 minutes to get our fried chicken. On the bright side, there's ample parking space available.
review 2: This restaurant is one of my option for getting my work done since the 2nd floor are so quiet and not a lot of people hanging around there. I dont like spicy food so the option is the richicken (chicken with cheese sauce) for 3 dollars (around idr 45k-50k) and snacks like fried cheese ball and ice cream or pink lava (coconut, milk, w/ pink syrup) for 1,2 dollar ( around idr 17k-20k). The 2nd floor rarely cleaned up so the table the near the stairs filled up with the leftover. Other than that, the place is clean and comfortable
review 3: For the cheese, chicken and spicy lovers. I just like the cheese and the desserts, it's served in a small cup, just a perfect size for not feeling too rich. Pity that many times they run out of it. My favorite is the Tiramisu Cake and the Lemon Curd Cheese Cake flavor after the BBQ Cheesy Wedges. I used to order from Gofood as my first visit to the outlet wasn't a good experience. A very long queue with one counter serving the customers and was extremely slow too.
review 4:
The fried chicken isn't special, even with cheese. I think it will be better if they use mozarella. I tried the hot chicken level 5th, I think the spicy taste come from pepper, this feels a little different from the spicy flavor of the chili. The strawbery milk is good. Over all I like it, but not special.

About the place, you will notice from the street, easy to find. In the first opening, this place waa crowded. The parking area is wide. The toilet is clean. If you want to see the street view you can eat at the second floor.
review 5: Good food and good service, but I feel a little bit narrow inside

name: Men-Ramen Gatsu
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.428, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: Delicious ramen, both the original and shoyu variants. Their chicken karaage is good too. The restaurant is much bigger than the Sanur branch. The parking space is also much bigger and convenient.
review 2: Having been there a countless times, I can definitely say this is my favorite ramen restaurant in Bali. The place is cosy and quite busy. The food is decently priced and tastes super delicious. Don't forget to order the hot moringa tea, it's refillable and tastes so fresh.
review 3: This place is more quiet than the one in sanur area, as well much more bigger.. for the food nothing to complain about.. always amazing! One of the best place to eat ramen in Bali üëç
review 4: The taste is good.. I tried the Tori Tantanmen. It was good and the spicy is still ok...
review 5: I got the tonkotsu original. The noodle & broth is light, but nothing special, got bored of the taste before finishing it. The noodles are a bit too soggy when it arrives, and the taste becomes bland. The half boiled egg has a very sweet body flavor. The meat itself cooked well, the taste has a hint of a balinese style smoked pork cutlet. The egg & meat is good on its own, but doesn't really go uniformly with the overall dish

name: Terrazza Steak House Bali
address: Jalan Gatot Subroto Barat.336E-F, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1:
Steak was great
Mashed potato was great

Place is ok.

Complimentary water might be a good option as in fact the place not a cheap warung. And small plastic water bottles are not good for health and nature
review 2:
Delicious yet affordable steakhouse in Denpasar.
They marinated the steak in BBQ sauce first, then a different sauce is served on the side.
Doneness was nice.
review 3: Terrazza offers a fantastic dining experience. The steak is perfectly cooked and incredibly flavorful. The onion rings are crispy and delicious, making a great side dish. The must try is their mushroom sauce, creamy, and absolutely delicious. Highly recommended for steak lovers.
review 4: A nice casual steakhouse in Denpasar! The steaks and salads are great for the price both taste and portion wise. We ordered lamb burger patty too which tastes great but a little bit too dry on the outside.
review 5: Local steak house restaurant but many foreigner coming here. Very comfort food restaurant for steak. The the Bone is quite affordable. Taste good. All the food are lekker! Parking is easy. Toilet is clean at the back. Steak very well cooked. I will definitely comeback. Don't expect kobe beef / wagyu high marbling here. But for australian and US beef you can come here. It's my few times coming back, before you can ask how many grams you want the meat. Now they only portioning for around 200gr except the T-Bone. The Bakmi actually nice too!

review 1: Thank you, Dapur Coklat Denpasar team, especially Nanda, for being super friendly and patiently give me best service and I will definitely come back again.
review 2: Chocolate heaven ;) one of the best place surrounding with relax atmosphere to enjoy chocolate. Many selections of cake variants.The staff are very warm, helpful and friendly.Thank you Dapur Cokelat ;)
review 3: Chilli'n and having some deserts on a hot day, a slice of chocolate cake and gelato. Nice place (indoor & outdoor) and helpful staff. Spacious and free parking.
review 4: Ambience atmosphere to dine in and take away, superb choco cakes and many more
review 5: Service was okay.. The most horrible cake served ever. The crunch isn't there. The cake so dry,  I could thow it on the floor so it crumbs like sand. Horrible

name: Po Dumpling Bali
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.411, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80118, Indonesia
review 1:
By far, this is the best Dumplings Restaurant that I ever visited in Bali !
The food is so delicious *chef kisses ü§å
We had the lunch set menu & fried rice for kids, and we enjoyed every bite of it!

The servers are warm, attentive, friendly & helpful.
Ambience are awesome too!

Everything on the menu looks amazing, I was having a hard time to decide what to order. But worry not, I'll come back to try more ;)
review 2: I am so happy that I found out this place serving decent dumplings that fix my craving during my vacation at Bali. They are currently having 1 for 1 promo for their dumplings from 4-6pm, value for money! Clean place, friendly staff, of course good food that make me will come back very soon! ü•∞ü•∞ Not to mention that their Zao Rou Fan is fantastic as well !
review 3:
Got to this place by a friend recommendation, and it turns out to be very good, there are many different good things to try here, not just dumplings, but also the dan dan noodles, the sweet and sour pork and also their braised pork belly (either in dry or soupy noodle version), and of course the many different types of dumplings and dimsum available(shrimp shumai and pork and chives are recommended).

For the best deal, look for their happy hours and come to get the better price for your food. Not to mention also the place, small but cozy, will definitely going back here again and again
review 4: Been coming here quite regularly and tried different menu. So far my favourite noodle is the wonton noodle, the pork & chives dumplings are good too! I love the noodle‚Äôs texture and their seasoning is just at the right amount. The staff and service is actually one of the things that made me come back. Will be coming for more and try some other :)
review 5: Comfort food and a good choice for a rainy night. The pork belly noodles and the dumplings were the bomb. The staff were nice, they asked us several times how the food was.

name: Golden Lamian
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto Barat No.455, Padangsambian Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: I visited one of the branches in Living World (Gatsu) on the LG Floor. The food was good. I like the soup. The place was not really big, it only provided 15 tables, so if it's full, you have to wait the line. The price was fine, yet the tax is too much. There was some promotions for some food. If you wanna have a noodle for dinner or lunch, come and have a visit.
review 2:
Yumm... Love the soup, pangsit and extra spicy seasoning, so tasty.. Cozy place, clean, indoor and outdoor seating, friendly and helpful staff. Offers interesting promo almost everyday, ooeemmjii..
Spacious and free parking.
review 3:
I give 5star and i hope there will be some improvement on the food. The food were okay, nothing special.
Service could be improved, the staffs are friendly and quick. But i was being asked 3 times if i want to dine in or take away. 1 time by the host, 2 times by the cashier.
Atmosphere, could be improve, it looks like a big place but could be optimized on the seatings.
review 4: It was my first time to eat here yet i was amazed with the staff cause they did a great job to pass all the information to new customers. The restaurant is very clean. We ordered the grills and it was yummy in our tummy! End up being a member of Golden Lamian cause their promos is not a joke! Keep up the good work!
review 5: Kindly to observe freshness of the food on display racks aspecially beef n meat base items. Don't let these happen to stay  competitive n success  Thank you.
